beer.beer_description:
Darker doesn’t always mean stronger. Red IPA's usually carry a maltiness that you don’t find with paler styles. The malt character can range from a light caramel to full on rich toffee and toast.

It has a wonderful fruit, pine and spice balance that develops on the palate. It has a firm bitterness, but the caramel sweetness rounds it out to ensure your senses aren’t overwhelmed.

Malt: Pale, munich, melanoidin, crystal, roasted barley, carapils
Hops: Simcoe, Mosaic, Hallertau Blanc
Appearance: Hazy, deep amber
Aroma: Tropical fruit, pine, citrus, earthy spice
Flavour	Tropical fruit, toffee, dank pine
Body: Medium-full

items.badge_description: Thanks for staying at home, and checking in with Untappd! It allows us to stay connected to a community of beer lovers, just like you, even if we can't be in the same physical location. From our home to yours, cheers and stay safe!

Canning is all the rage and it's not hard to see why - travels well, more environmentally friendly, and no need to carry your bottle opener. That's 340 checkins with the serving style of Can. Try 5 more for Level 69! Want to learn more about this badge? Check out our podcast
